headline: Agilent (A): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q4 Earnings?
summary: Although the S&P 500 is down 1% over the past six months, Agilent’s stock price has fallen further to $116.86, losing shareholders 10.3% of their capital. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
